      <section name='pegasus'>

         <para number='1' comment='Ride pegasus - loc 588'>
         You climb onto the back of this legendary beast, and dig your heels into his sides. "Gee up, horsey," you cry. Nothing happens, but then, you woudn't expect it to, because he's dead. Such a vicious, dangerous creature when he was alive, who would have thought he'd ever allow anyone on his back?
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='roomex'>
         You hear a sudden cry of "Gee up, horsey!" Looking around, you discover that %s has climbed onto the back of the legendary beast and is riding him. Such a vicious, dangerous creature as the winged horse would never have allowed this when he was alive!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='priest'>

         <para number='1' comment='hello'>
         The priest acknowledges your greeting with a nod. "How can I help you, %s?"
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='job/work (1)'>
         "I am the priest and councelor attached to this temple.", he explains. "We do not hold services as such, worship is by individual contemplation."
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='job/work (2)'>
         "My job is to look after the shrine and to provide councel to the worshipers. I also," he smiles, "answer the questions of the curious who visit the shrine to find out more. However, we are not a proselyting organisation, so missionary activity is not called for."
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='temple'>
         "The temple is, as near as we can tell, a replica of the inside of one of the Martian spaceships. We have explored the ruins extensively, and the design is based on frescos and blueprints found in the ruins."
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Cult (1)'>
         "Our Cult is based on the revelations of the prophet Gaelaan. We are a peaceful people, but unfortunately there are those of our foes who are far from peaceful, and on a number of occasions we have had to defend our members against outside violence.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Cult (2)'>
         "You can read more about the Cult of Gaelaan in our Encyclopedia Galactica entry at http://www.ibgames.net/fed2/galactica/gaelaan.html"
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Gaelaan'>
         "The prophet Gaelaan was taken from us some years ago. We do not know exactly what happened, but we believe that he has gone before us."
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='venus'>
         The priest looks thoughtful. "We have been lucky on Venus, a political alliance with the Venus Freedom Party has allowed us to openly establish the shrine. Sadly things are not so easy elsewhere. On Selena, for instance, the Cult is subject to repression, and worship is, by necessity, clandestine."
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='bye'>
         The priest bows graciously and returns to his contemplation.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='nomatch'>
         The priest shakes his head regretfully. "I'm sorry, I can't help you with that.", he tells you.
         </para>

      </section>

