      <section name='zork'>

         <para number='1' comment='hello'>
         "Wotcha guv!" says the droid in an excruciating cockney accent. "Wot can I do you for?" It smirks, takes a swig of its coffee, and stares at you expectantly, ocular units swiveling to look at you from different angles.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='bye'>
         The droid waves an appendage in a casual manner. "'Ave-a-noice-day-guv," it says, running all the words together.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='nomatch'>
         "'Fraid I can't 'elp you with that one, guv," it says in an infuriatingly cheerful tone of voice.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='cockney'>
         "Manufactured within the sound of the Bow Bells!" the droid declares proudly. "All my assembly siblings have these accents. Blimey - some of 'em even became Pearly Droids!"
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='pearly'>
         "Pearly Droids? They are an important piece of history. Blimey, what do they teach at schools these days? There's an entry about them in the Encyclopedia Galactica at http://www.ibgames.net/fed2/galactica/pearly.html." The droid zooms its ocular sensors slowly in and out, in the droid equivalent of shaking its head.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='job/work/profession [1]'>
         "I'm a dayta-input-droid," it says proudly, slurring the words together in a way that makes it difficult to understand. "The Company, Hermes Insurance, handles life insurance in this neck of the woods. I record the number of deaths for each punter."
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='job/work/profession [2]'>
         Its ocular sensors give you a sly, sideways look. "Of course, for a suitable consideration, I might just be able to reduce the number of deaths for someone. Let's say a reduction in the number of deaths by five in return for a slithy tove?" You notice that the cockney accent has mysteriously vanished.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='insurance'>
         "Painfully expensive, isn't it guv?" It sounds very cheerful, but then it's not the droid's money. It lowers its voice, "For a small consideration - say a slithy tove - I could reduce the number of deaths on your record by five..." It raises an appendage. "For you I would do it for free, but the union won't let me. Honest guv, would I lie to you?"
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='london [1]'>
         "Ah! Lundun!" The droid's ocular sensors mist over as it remembers its home. "Of course, fings-ain't-wot-they-use-ta-be." You rather wish it would stop running the words together - the accent is difficult enough to follow even when the words are separated.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='london [2]'>
         "I used to be a cab driver you know. Fings went downhill when they allowed those foreign robots from Slough in... it was all the fault of the govmint... I once had Ming in the back of my cab, before he was the big boss, of course... congestion charging... total nightmare... how can anyone be expected..." You find your concentration drifting as the droid's tirade washes over you.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='london [3]'>
         "...so after that I'd had enough, and I moved here and got this job working in life insurance." It stops, a bit like a run down clockwork toy. You jerk yourself back to reality and make some suitably sympathetic noises.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='venus'>
         "S'OK, if you like that sort of fing," it tells you. "The politics here is very weird, wot wiv the Lib-ray-shun Party and that funny Cult of Gaylin. I stay well clear and try to keep my olfactory sensors clean."
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='beverage/coffee'>
         Somehow or other the droid manages to look furtive. "Coffee isn't illegal," it tells you defensively. "THEY" - you can hear the capitals in its voice - "want to ban it, but doing that would cause riots so they jus' put 'toxic substance' labels on the containers. I like to add some machine oil and a couple of drops of WD40 to keep the parts all moving in harmony."
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='gaelaan/gaylin'>
         "That lot? Bunch o' loonies!"
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='union/thwap'>
         The droid preens itself. "I," it informs you proudly, "am a fully paid up member of the union -  The Helpful Workers Alliance for Progress." Seeing that you look mystified it tells you that THWAP is a system-wide union for non-organics working in the data industry. "Of course," it adds, "I would like to be in the stevedore's union, but that's not possible..."
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='stevedor'>
         "Everyone wants to be a stevedore," it tells you. "It's hard work, but well paid, and the, errrm, fringe benefits have to be seen to be believed. But you can't be a stevedore unless you are in their union. And you can't be in the union unless you are a stevedore. The jobs are heirlooms inherited by the children." The droid sighs deeply and lapses into a brooding silence.
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='ming'>
         "Now there was someone who knew what he wanted!" exclaims the droid admiringly. "Did I tell you I once had him the back of my cab? Before he became emperor, of course. I remember it well - one of the mark IV assault robots he was using for security ate the cab fenders. But I have to say he was well spoken and paid for the damage - a real gent!"
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='bribe command [start]'>
         Your proffered slithy tove certificate is accepted by the droid and rapidly vanishes from sight. "Wait here," says the droid. "I'll fix it while everyone is on their break." The droid oozes round the door and vanishes from sight for a few minutes.
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='bribe command [finish]'>
         After what seems like a long time, but is, in reality, only a few minutes, the droid reappears. "Done," it tells you. "I knocked five deaths off your record. A-pleasure-to-do-business-wiv-a-toff-like-you." With that it ambles over to the group taking their break, and joins in the conversation.
         </para>

         <para number='20' comment='bribe [no slithy]'>
         "Sorry guv. The union would have me disassembled if it found out I'd fixed a record wivout bein' paid the going rate -- one slithy to shave five deaths off the record."
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='try to enter loc 206'>
         You move towards the open door. "Oi! Waddja-think-you're-doin', guv". The zork857 droid bars your way with an extensor, "This is the private property of Hermes Insurance. Employees only!"
         </para>

      </section>

